-- Gabon’s Opposition-Owned TV Station Attacked, AFP Reports
-- B y   P a u l i n e   B a x
-- 2012-08-17T10:23:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-17/gabon-s-opposition-owned-tv-station-attacked-afp-reports.html
A television station owned by
Gabon’s main opposition leader, Andre Mba Obame, was attacked by
masked gunmen yesterday, Agence France-Presse reported, citing
director Frank Nguema.  About 15 unidentified men broke into the building of TV+ in
the capital, Libreville, and set the transmitters on fire,
according to AFP said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pauline Bax in Accra at 
 pbax@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
